					<h2>Before You Build, Remodel, or Even Dream—Ask the Right Questions
</h2>				
							<ul>
							<li>
										 Is your layout functional for you—and for the next buyer or tenant?
									</li>
								<li>
										 Will your design meet appraisal standards and boost property value?
									</li>
								<li>
										 Are you maximizing natural light, privacy, and flow—or creating expensive regrets?
									</li>
								<li>
										 How will your finishes and materials affect rental income or long-term maintenance?
									</li>
								<li>
										 Do you have a designer who collaborates with your lender—not just your vision? The right design isn’t just about style—it’s about strategy.
									</li>
						</ul>
					<h2>Why Design Matters in Wealth Building
</h2>				
							<ul>
							<li>
										Add bedrooms or baths without expanding the footprint
									</li>
								<li>
										Improve appraisal comps with better layouts
									</li>
								<li>
										Boost Airbnb appeal (and nightly rates) with thoughtful touches
									</li>
								<li>
										Make rental units more livable = fewer vacancies = more income
									</li>
								<li>
										Increase resale potential with features buyers actually want
